parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch Failure Causing Vehicle Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause a vehicle fire, potentially leading to serious injury or death, as well as significant property damage.
symptoms: with smoke and flames emanating from the underhood area or steering column. In some cases
the horn may sound before the fire is noticed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deterioration of the transmission linkage grommet can cause a loss of power to the transmission's third and overdrive gears, resulting in the inability to shift into high speeds, which can lead to reduced vehicle performance and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Loss of power to transmission's third and overdrive gears
inability to shift into high speeds

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accelerator pedal sticking in an open position can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or stuck in an open position
